text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: i’m wrapping up transcriptions for the first batch of leaves for #thesurvivortreeproject: the last few will be posted this week. transcribing these first twelve survivor stories sent me on a journey that i never could have anticipated. i knew that this endeavor would be unlike anything i’d ever set out to create; but nothing could have prepared me for the metamorphosis it would begin in me, or how deeply grateful other survivors would be as they received this work. healing is not a solitary process- it can’t be. the deeper i wade into survivor advocacy work, the more i understand that we need *each other* to do this (i can’t even tell you definitively what “this” is; but if you’re a survivor, you know). i’ve always been an introvert and stubbornly individual: i like to travel alone, live alone, spend time alone, and i find myself single most of the time. and for the past 20+ years- since i was first abused- i’ve thought i could heal alone as well. how wrong i was. and how joyous a realization that is! through these unique connections, this project has for the first time made me feel empowered *because* of my survivorship. though it is still by no means easy (and i’m still adhering strictly to self-care and mental wellness plans), i no longer feel that my survivorship is a personal disability. and that’s huge for me. just typing those words has me sobbing tears of joy and taking big gulps of revitalizing oxygen after i’ve felt that i couldn’t breathe for so long. i hope to continue to grow in this work. i hope to continue to grow in this community. i want this hope and this growth for *all* survivors. ✨🌱 #selflove #love #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #csasurvivor #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mentalwellness #selfie #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #thesurvivortreeproject #artist
name: Mel Hanley | Survivor Advocate

text:
// sex, healing trauma & open heart surgery // this was hands down the most empowering, healing & body love’n experience ever!

i haven’t always loved my body. in fact i’ve had an unhealthy relationship with it for most of my life. it mostly came through lack of worth, distorted understandings of beauty as a teenager, violence and sexual trauma, which i experienced in my early adult years. i, like many women i know can declare #metoo.

facing open heart surgery made me develop a new found appreciation for this marvellous vehicle that houses my soul. i love it in ways i never have before.

this photoshoot was one of the bravest things i have done in my healing journey. i never in my life imagined i’d be strutting around half naked in front of a camera. but i loved it!

it was one of the ways i psychologically prepared for surgery. slightly unconventional, i know! but i thought i’d get the practice in for when i’m a real open heart lingerie model! 😝

i now have a 15cm scar down my chest. but you know what?! i love my body even more with the scar. it is the most amazing mark of love and life that i can imagine. it is a permanent reminder of what it truly means to live life with an open heart — physically, mentally, emotionally and spiritually.

the world would be different if we all opened our hearts. and took a scalpel to our societal and psychological conditioning. if we moved beyond the labels. and viewed the world through our hearts. rather than our minds. if we saw souls instead of bodies. gosh, could you imagine?

r x

text:
today we celebrate and honor the life and work of poet maya angelou, the author of more than 30 books and the recipient of more than 50 honorary degrees.
•
•

before becoming a writer she had many different jobs including a cook, waitress, sex-worker, dancer, actor, playwright, editor at an english-language newspaper in egypt, calypso singer, cast member of the opera porgy and bess, and as san francisco’s first female african-american cable car conductor. maya angelou was also one of the first african-american female members in the directors guild of america.
•
•
her first book, i know why the caged bird sings, is as relevant now as it was then. (content warning: sexual assault)
•
•
decades before the #metoo and #timesup movements brought survivors of sexual assault greater visibility and solidarity, maya angelou wrote in her 1969 memoir about her own experience with sexual trauma and how her mom’s boyfriend raped her when she was a child.
•
•
though some banned the book because of the rape scene, maya angelou expressed in an interview how she believed the book had saved lives by providing a model of endurance, “the encountering may be the very experience which creates the vitality and the power to endure.”
•
•
oprah winfrey, (a recent #dailyherstory feature herself) has called angelou a mentor, and said that “maya angelou is not what she has done or written or spoken, it’s how she did it all. she moved through the world with unshakeable calm, confidence, and a fiery, fierce grace and abounding love.”
•
•
even after death, maya angelou continues to inspire many and her life and words are powerful. we encourage you to read her work and live as fully as she did.
•
•
#comment your favorite maya angelou #poem or #book! •
•
•
•
•

text:
a big part of psychology research in history was aimed at understanding the evolutionary differences between male and female brains in order to explain the evolutionary need for biological differences.
🧠 at first, scientists attributed the size of a man’s frontal lobe to explain their believed superior intelligence, and used creation theory (the story of adam and eve) to justify a woman’s perceived emotional affectability. 👨‍🔬 there was even a german scientist who claimed that a man’s intelligence allowed their emotions to affect them less. he also purported that if women were as intelligent as men, their emotional affectability would destroy the human race (in the same way that eve was believed to have caused the fall from grace)
————————————————
but why is a study comparing male and female brains important?
————————————————
since feminist research methods were introduced, we started challenging some of the beliefs we have developed over time. we have since learned that biologically, men and women are equal, but a lot of the beliefs that these studies developed are still present in our gender norms and gender stereotypes:
♟ logic continues to be the desired trait, and people generally look down at you if you’re too “emotional”. while the idea around men and women’s intelligence is slowly changing, women are generally challenged on their qualifications, are generally believed to be less qualified than male counterparts, whereas most men aren’t generally second guessed on their qualifications.
🤰women are still believed to be intrinsically motivated to reproduce even though it takes two to create life. the idea that men deeply desire children is not something we generally believe.
————————————————
so what can we do about it?
————————————————
1️⃣ start reflecting about your own personal gender assumptions:
• what do you believe?
• what have you experienced?
• where did i learn to make these assumptions?
.
2️⃣ be conscious in your assumptions:
• am i acting in a way that supports these gender norms?
• is this contributing to the development and affirmations of gender norms in others?
name: AB Wild Rose Feminist Alliance

text:
home sick today. i was exhausted. i’m run down, hadn’t slept much at all last night. had chest pains. so i decided to watch the much talked about #bohemianrhapsody. i’ll be honest, i’m not the biggest fan of queen. i like some of their music, but it’s not like i’ve got their entire discography. i just know their hits and that’s about it.
•
then, we have that terrible situation of separating the artist from the art. directed by #bryansinger. a man who is in hot water currently due to multiple accounts of sexual assault. rumours have been circulating since i was a teenager. i remember perez hilton writing articles about it, years ago. now, in the #metoo and the #timesup movement. his deeds are coming back to bite him in the ass. so i wasn’t exactly interested in the film. i decided to bite the bullet and give it a watch.
•
did i love it? no. #ramimalek is a fantastic actor. i think he’s gone method with this performance. he is embodying what i believe to be the musical genius #freddiemercury. he looks like he has given it his all here. it’s the highlight of the film for me.
•
the music is also great. i loved the visuals in the film. there is a lot of great visual queues and transitions in the film. i can’t fault bryan singer and his vision here. i think this did look really well made. years working on massive budgeted superhero and action films have given him a chance to add some flair to this film. let’s be honest though, is it #burlesque? no. i’d rather watch that a million times over than this film.
•
i also wanted to say that, i really would have liked to see what #sachabaroncohen would have done with the role. i reckon he would’ve have gone to the darker places that this film didn’t. early talk said he wanted to really tackle the gay themes and freddie’s #aids diagnosis. i think he would’ve been braver in the role. he’s an actor who never seems afraid. i think he would have even filmed gay sex scenes if the script he had worked on would have called for it. this version of the film is glitzy and glamorous, but all of the #lgbt stuff feels glossed over.
•
if you’ve seen the film, what did you think of it? let me know in the comments.
•
#musical #drama #movies

text:
an oppressor doesn't always know they are oppressing. which can be confusing to the victim, on top of the harm the oppression is causing. so many times it becomes the victims job to speak up and tell their story - which can be hard to identify with the thought "why would anyone do that?" flying through one's head.
speak up for yourself and speak up for those who don't have the words.
.
this snapart depicts a person i admire. someone strong, someone who speaks up for themself, someone resilient.
i love you.
.

text:
trauma is rooted in the sense of not feeling seen and heard. in our groundswell surf therapy for trauma recovery sessions surfsisters are seen, heard, and celebrated as they surf into the healing of old trauma wounds, are empowered to express their truest self in the world, and supported in a united surf sisterhood!
🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️
register now for our san diego, oc, and san fransisco surf therapy sessions for the summer of 2019! and see how surfing with in the safe and brave community of sisterhood can help you overcome trauma, abuse, addiction, depression, and anxiety! we are all in recovery to our truest selves! come surf with us!
🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️🏄🏽‍♀️

text:
french women put on defence in post-#metoo defamation trial
#
paris - a former french lawmaker’s defamation lawsuit against six women who accused him of sexual misconduct and four journalists who reported the allegations goes to trial monday in what some fear illustrates a backlash against the #metoo movement.nearly 1 1/2 years before allegations against hollywood producer harvey weinstein became a reckoning event for powerful men in entertainment and media, france’s mediapart website and radio station france inter published accounts from 14 women who alleged denis baupin had groped, sexted and otherwise harassed them.in this nov. 18, 2017 file photo, french secretary of state for women's rights marlene schiappa delivers a speech in chassieu, near lyon, central france. twelve women, journalists and witnesses go on trial monday feb. 4, 2019, for alleged defamation of prominent french lawmaker denis baupin after their accusations of sexual misconduct forced his resignation, although baupin denied any misconduct, and marlene schiappa has said she would not specifically comment on the case because it's up to justice to decide. (laurent cipriani, file / ap photo)baupin, a prominent green party member and former paris city official, resigned as vice-president of the lower house of parliament when the reports came out in may 2016. he denied wrongdoing and the…

text:
the back hammer fist on the boomerang app 🤗✊🏻
.
.
.
this is a little teaser to the full back hammer fist tutorial (coming soon!).
.
.
.
here are some key points:
✅ using the side of your fist is a less fragile surface area to strike with.
✅ this is highly effective when targeting the face of an assailant.
✅ you can easily raise or lower the back hammer fist to adapt to various heights
✅ there are more hammer fist variations to learn such as the down hammer fist..
.
.
.
‼️ please note this is a boomerang video so you don’t see the whole strike from start to finish. after striking the target, you want to immediately drop the elbow so that your hand can quickly guard the upper body as your return to your stance.
.
.
.
excited for the next post 🤗.
.

😢 deep & #realaf, exactly why #imangry 😡🤬 #myanger is more than #justified, #devil’s #whitepawns, the #victimized{still being victimized today/#2019}are #victims...don’t wanna be, disgusting to invoke we’re “playing”🤔😡 maybe to u sick #racist, the oppression ur gov put us through, is some kind of 😷 game to you😤#repost @bstreets80 with @make_repost
・・・
today in #blackhistory we honor the #silence 
we the silent screams of our foremothers
the screams swallowed 
while we were raped 
the screams tucked into the darkest places 
of our #souls 
so as not to #wake the #children 
and see more #horror in their eyes 
so as not to wake the #men 
and see the #pain of not being able to protect us 
the emasculation of being powerless 
when master rapes your wife 
we the sobs hushed 
we the refrains muffled 
we the words that didn’t part from our teeth 
because 
we did best to know our place 
we did best not to be uppity 
or think that we may deserve dignity 
we that learned a down cast eye 
kept us alive 
we the tears flowing like waterfalls 
perpetually inside 
while our sons swung 
high 
and died 
our feet bleed beneath our skin 
our backs shredded within 
our lips closed and tight 
our tongue tattooed with perpetual bite 
we learned to suffer in silence to save ourselves
to save our men and children 
we learned too well 
we the tired 
we the weary
we the screams
we the sirens
we are silent no more 
you will hear us 
our feet marching 
with the screams of our ancestors at our backs 
like wind in our sails 
vengeance that has laid waiting for too long 
we will open our mouths 
and you will never hear the same again 
our screams will echo in your souls forever 
our #metoo began before hollywood 
before trump grabbed pussies 
stand with your alabaster tears 
for as long as you can 
but move when you hear my army 
move when you hear my battle cry 
move when you feel the presence of my lineage 
silent no more  #queens#kings#blackhistory #divineintuition#blackconsciousness #blackunity 
#thingstheydontteach 
#africa#blackandproud
#silentnomore  #weareourancestorswildestdreams

text:
it's so crazy to say that having a blood clot after the surgery was the best thing that ever happened to me but the extra complications made me require a full time care giver! i was able to fly my brother out and it's the most amazing gift from the universe! being in malibu with pete is absolutely perfect, it was our dream to be healthy and wealthy and it's happening! he inspired me to quit drinking and we focused on transformation with wellness. it's so random we are here together as i celebrate two years sober and financial freedom with the person who inspired the entire thing 💓 the process certainly wasn't easy and there have been many many rough patches along the way, change is hard but we are strong 💪 
when i saw the way people were treating my brother as he struggled with sobriety i was infuriated. everyone told me he would always be a drunk and to never let him live in your home, alcoholic people are all the same, etc. i knew this wasn't true and gave him holistic healing and a place to recover from the alcohol abuse and hand injury he suffered that was calm and safe. eventually i realized that i was the same, unable to stop drinking alcohol and the only difference between us was that i simply had been lucky not to have serious consequences yet. 
i used my insurance benefits for recovery and was open and honest about it with every person in my management because i was so grateful for the opportunity to heal that my brother never got. he doesn't have insurance and could never afford treatment in malibu so i took the entire process incredibly seriously because i know how lucky and rare it is to have the opportunity to work with talented therapists and have the time off work. i share everything i learned on here and for people like my brother who don't have access and am working on my book proposal this month as i recover to share my simplified approach to sobriety!

#liveyourtruth #soberyogi #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #addictionrecovery #onedayatatime #soberaf

text_retweet:
repost @muslimahnewsid / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

.

سی سال این روزنامه را اداره میکنه حسینیه می خواد بزنه کاخ سفید و خیلی کارهای دیگه 
شریعتمداری ؛ واحد پول ایالات متحده آمریکا دلار است 
البته سخنان سخیف آیشان سبب خیرشد و خانم عبادی بعد این جریانات برنده جایزه صلح نوبل شدن 
وخانم ستوده وکیل پایه یک دادگستری در زندان هستند و شریعتمداری در کیهان البته روز ها در روزنامه کیهان شبها در کهکشان یعنی تو یه دنیای دیگه سیر میکند

text:
_______________________________________жить в тоске зелёной – это слишком!
счастья нет, и всё идёт не в масть?
точат беспокойные мыслишки – 
не давайте им торжествовать.

стоит ли терзаться понапрасну,
слёзы лить по всякой ерунде!
улыбнёмся – всё равно прекрасна
жизнь «незамечательных» людей.

непреложна истина смешная:
мы как есть, по сути, состоим
из того, что жить, порой, мешает,
от чего избавиться хотим.

надо, коль печали сердце сушат,
зёрна отделить от половы.
смысл жизни отыскать, а лучше –
выкинуть его из головы.

и тогда найдёте своё счастье,
ну а чтоб найти наверняка,
напрямую можно обращаться –
жду к себе на «чашку кофейка»
владимир котиков. 
#психология #psychology #психологическаяпомощь #psychological_hрelp
#притча##праздник #счастье#любовь#семья #мысли#философия #высказывания#печаль #грусть#psyxogram#love #cool#metoo#доброеутро

…

text: the morrigan is the celtic goddess of war, fate, change,magic and death. she is stunningly beautiful and stands proud and strong for those who she loves. ive never really beleived in gods and goddesses but theres something different to me about the morrigan. a few years back i started having really vivid dreams of a celtic woman with long dark hair, with wings of raven black and scores of crows surrounding her. she was always fighting and she was wild and furious and a force to be reckoned with. i just stumbled across the name morrigan. in times of stress and pain i would see my spirit animal the crow and it would bring me a sense of comfort. she called out to me in my darkest of times and she brought me a sense of comfort and a fighting spirit. in magical  workings she helps to bring truth to the surface, she helps you to see the darkest parts of you and make them bearable to live with. she personally helped me to speak my truth, to speak out and to look my demons right in the face and be powerful. and thats why i believe she is real, or all she stands for was represented in her spirit to me. thankyou so much @rhi82bee for getting me this gorgeous statue of her for me for my birthday. you can never know how much it means to me and how close to my heart you are to me. you are such an incredible wild woman and im so lucky to have found you, you trully are an incredible friend and such a beautiful soul. xx thankyou ❤️ #spiritualstrength #witchesofinstagram #witchythings #pagan #pagansofinstagram #wicca #wiccansofinstagram #witchessociety #thewitchesmoonbox #themorrigan #celticgoddesses #celtic #magic #goddess #wildwoman #ptsd #suicideawarness #metoo #speakingout #strength #fightingback #livingmytruth #spiritual #meanttomeetagain #deity #goddessofwar #witchcraft #thankful #birthdaygifts

milk and honey is a collection of poetry and prose about survival. it is about the experience of violence, abuse, love, loss, and femininity. it is split into four chapters, and each chapter serves a different purpose, deals with a different pain, heals a different heartache. milk and honey takes readers through a journey of the most bitter moments in life and finds sweetness in them because there is sweetness everywhere if you are just willing to look.

text:
i was recently honored to have my sexual assault story included in @bossladycreates #thesurvivortreeproject and i have emotions! all of the emotions, to be exact.

i've known #bossladycreates for almost 5 years (whaaaaat!) and in that time, she has become like my big sister. constantly teaching me new things, supporting my crazy ideas, laughing at my chaotic humor, propping me up emotionally when i just...can't, and (most importantly) encouraging and supporting me as a fellow survivor on my journey. i am blessed to know someone as kind and compassionate as mel. 
i urge all of you to visit her page to read her story and learn about the #thesurvivortreeproject and why it was started. thank you @bossladycreates for including my story with so many other powerful stories of survival!
.
.
.

text:
i’m thankful for all those out there doing this much need work in arresting these criminals and in rescuing these girls but my genuine concern is what happens to these young girls afterwards? 
who helps them heal? what kind of holistic therapies are being offered to them? who supports them if there families have disowned them? what skill set do they have to go back into the world and lead a successful life? what happens if their credit has been trashed by their pimps? where do they get money when all the money they made was taken by their pimps? how do they go see a dentist? get enrolled back into college or finish high school? who takes care of their children while they rehabilitate back into society? 
these are just a few of the things i needed assistance with and had no one to turn to. this is why i formed beyond freedom non profit because going from a product to a person shouldn’t be a solo job, it takes a community. be the solution. message me if god is calling you to serve in this way.

text:
what’s the difference between “traveling” and living out of your car?

when you travel, you don’t worry about where your next meal is going to come from.

from may-september of 2018, i lived out of my car with my volatile ex-boyfriend.

we moved out of the house my parents had generously rented for us and began living on the road. i thought i was tired of staying in one place, but let’s face it - i was tired of the way he treated me. i thought that if we changed the way we lived, he might change his treatment of me. 
a word of advice: don’t add instability to your unhealthy relationships expecting positive change. 
after five months of screaming violence that seemed it would never end, my parents saved me. that’s right, it was a full-blown rescue mission.

now i wear my dad’s overalls. i listen to my own music - which is not “boring”, it’s actually quite good. i walk with my dogs and talk with my extended family.

if you’re in a situation where you feel unappreciated, leave. don’t worry what anyone will think, just get out. and if you feel like you’re already in too deep, talk to your friends. tell them what you’re going through. 
none of us deserves to suffer alone. #metoo

text: discurso de arantxa etxevarría en los goya 2019 recogido por @elhuffpost. imposible perderse estas palabras. «"creo que una sociedad hay que medirla por el sitio donde está la mujer. tenemos que pensar mucho si españa es suficientemente madura", ha empezado diciendo la cineasta. "querría dedicarle esta película, que es de amor, a todos aquellos que no permiten amar diferente, a aquellos que no son capaces de ponerse en la piel de la minoría y del distinto", ha señalado. "a aquellos que creen que no es necesaria una ley de violencia de género, aquellos que piensan que no se necesita apoyo del colectivo lgtbi. a los que piensan que el aborto no es parte de la sanidad pública. aquellos que creen que el cambio de sexo no debería estar en la sanidad pública", ha enfatizado. text:
i had a really hard day yesterday that involved being physically intimidated and gaslit by an older, white man. it began when he tried to encroach on the space / time of the art group i help facilitate. then he reached out and patted a friend, an older woman, on the shoulder in an overly familiar way. .
when i told him to please stop touching her, it wasn't ok and it was patronizing, i got the stare. the stare from a white man that tells me i need to get back in my place. or else.
. 
i told him to knock that off too. we then had an impasse at a flight of stairs; i felt unsafe going ahead of him. he balked and was rude in response to my gesture that he take the stairs first while saying, "after you.", insisting go first. i refused and he took off for another set of stairs.
.
minutes later he's physically trying to keep me from getting into the building's office ahead of him. i push him out and close the door, saying loudly, "no!". he then pushed open the door again until i jumped over, pushed him out and locked it. .
when i open it to let him in he brings on the gaslight, saying, "we only came in to ask if we could set up some chairs...", casting me in the role of hysterical woman.
.
my anxiety is still amped up, my stress-response system still in what a friend called "mama bear mode". my friend is still processing, the unwelcome touch from a belligerent man taking her back decades to a violent ex-husband. .
some comments in our group are so haunting me today. .
one woman noted that she thought he was rude, but "it wasn't that big a deal and it's easier to let it go." this both left me feeling gaslit, just another woman overreacting, and also furious about the behavior women are taught to minimize and work around. when she found out how physical he became with me up at the office she was pretty horrified and walked back her earlier comments.
. 
one woman noted she never stands up for herself or others because she's afraid of how far it might escalate, "what if he'd had a gun?", she said. .
continued in comments.

text_retweet:
#repost many thanks to the awesome women @jointhecosmos for selecting me as 1 of 15 asian women creators to showcase at your upcoming new year market event!  i’m getting ready with new designs + #janetjewelry hits. and i’m sharing a space with @fmmtj, the fab new jewelry line by my former assistant, phoebe. cu there! ・・・
✨ welcome to our #cosmosvendorspotlight series! every day until the cosmos new year market on 2/9, we’ll be featuring one of 15 asian women vendors. grab your tix today, link in bio! ✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
❣️does your asian american identity inform your work/business? if so, how?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i identify most with my father, a 2nd generation japanese american, who spent his teen years at camp manzanar. my dad went from living in a concentration camp, to being ranked the in the top 25 asian american entrepreneurs in america.  his work philosophy and work ethics, his optimism even during times of extreme hardships, his desire to give back to the community (his foundation’s main focus is to provide scholarships to underprivileged students)—it is rooted in his japanese american experience/identity, and that foundation is what drives me and my business.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
❣️how do you stay motivated and/or creative while running a business?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i make time every morning to do a quick am reflection for the day.  it helps me prioritize my day, while also entertaining my adhd brain, which is where most of my creativity dwells.  reflections help me connect the dots so that i can maintain focus on the big picture.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
❣️tell us about your dream project/collaborator.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“my dream project thus far, has been the one design i made for @iamwomankind, a non-profit org that helps survivors of gender based violence heal from their trauma.  i love that clients have told me it has been a conversation starter for them to talk to others about #metoo and #timesup. for a jewelry designer to have that kind of impact on a social justice issue close to my heart—that has been a dream come true for me, and i hope to be able to continue this passion project for as long as i can.”

text: “don’t forget, you’re just an object”. here we are in 2019, over a 100 years after the suffragette movement and there are still men who think it is acceptable, and worse truthful, to make comments like this. in a world where women prime ministers exist, in a world where women are being nominated and awarded prizes such as the noble peace prize, in a world where women are finally being seen for who they are and not what they are; we exist in a world where comments like that can be made!  we have come a long way but i defy anyone to say we have equality when young men see women as objects. we must continue the fight, we must educate, we must speak out. men must educate their fellow man. and women must respect themselves as they wish others to respect them. women are not objects. men are not objects. we are all human together. #metoo #womenarenotobjects #feminism #standup #wearehumantogether
name: Harriet Russ
